Very simple.<p>Either:<p><pre><code>    $copy = $original;
</code></pre>
Or, if you must have a function,<p><pre><code>    function array_copy(array $a) {
        return $a;
    }
</code></pre>
Arrays use the normal copy-on-write semantics of PHP. They are not passed by reference or object handle...<p>The only potential issue is if the array contains references deeper in.
